        </div>
      
      </div>
    

  


</div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1553720957792_39344"><div class="sqs-block-content"><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;"><em>Enjoy what you just read? Please help spread the word to new readers by sharing it on social media.</em></p></div></div><div class="sqs-block horizontalrule-block sqs-block-horizontalrule" data-block-type="47" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1553720957792_38288"><div class="sqs-block-content"><hr /></div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1553720957792_38350"><div class="sqs-block-content"><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;"><em>Header Image: Marines clear buildings at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms. (Marine Corps Photo)</em>  </p></div></div><div class="sqs-block horizontalrule-block sqs-block-horizontalrule" data-block-type="47" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1553720957792_35100"><div class="sqs-block-content"><hr /></div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1553720957792_35163"><div class="sqs-block-content"><h3 style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Notes:</h3><p style="white-space:pre-wrap;">[1] Ian T. Brown, <em>A New Conception of War: John Boyd, the U.S. Marines, and Maneuver Warfare</em> (Quantico: Marine Corps University Press). Pg. 187.</p></div></div></div></div></div>
      
